  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3f17274109eb96d4eb175c0a9a486f69, type: 3}
  m_Name: CombatTraining
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  featName: Combat Training
  desc: You can choose and take a number of <b><i>Martial Maneuvers</b></i> equal
    to your <b><i>Talent</b></i> score.  By expending one <b><i>AP</b></i> you can
    change your <b><i>Stance</b></i>, while fighting with a weapon. You choose your
    first stance at the beginning of the combat.  <br> - <b>Tree Stance:</b> The
    default <b><i>Stance</b></i> No additional features. A <b><i>Stance</b></i> most
    warriors are taught first. <br> - <b>Waves Stance:</b> If you are holding only
    one weapon and the other hand is free, your main weapon gains one additional
    meter of range. A <b><i>Stance</b></i> often used by duelists and rogues. <br>
    - <b>Stone Stance:</b> You lose one <b><i>AP</b></i>, but instead gain one <b><i>Reaction</b></i>
    A defensive <b><i>Stance</b></i> focused on reacting, rather than attacking.
    <br> - <b>Flame Stance:</b> You lose one <b><i>Reaction</b></i> but instead gain
    one additional <b><i>AP</b></i> An offensive <b><i>Stance</b></i> that focuses
    on attacking rather than reacting. <br> - <b>Iron Stance:</b> You hold the weapon
    in two hands. Attacks made with this weapon cost one less <b><i>AP</b></i> two
    less <b><i>Stamina</b></i> points, and you use a larger damage. A <b><i>Stance</b></i>
    used by noble knights and powerful warriors.
